{
  "texts": [
    "Firstly, we illustrate climate interconnectedness from one country to the next for our large sample of countries using generalised temperature spillover indices from Diebold and Yilmaz (2012), which is also order invariant.",
    "Our evidence suggests that temperature changes have experienced spillovers from one country to the next, indicating the interconnectedness of these countries.",
    "In essence, connectedness motivates the notion that there are common factors in temperature changes.",
    "Given this global interconnectedness, it is critical to model common factors of climate when assessing its impact on macroeconomic activity.",
    "Our second contribution is to consider the impact of climate variability upon real GDP growth by differentiating between the impact of global climate risk and country specific climate risk using a factor model."
  ]
}